What is a good example of someone showing leadership skills?
A great leader is able to inspire others, motivate them towards achieving shared goals, and effectively manage resources to accomplish objectives. They also demonstrate integrity, accountability, empathy, compassion, and maintain strong interpersonal relationships with their team members. One such real-life example would be someone like former US President Barack Obama who was known for his ability to unite people from different backgrounds, his charisma in persuading others, his careful consideration of public welfare when making decisions, and the way he consistently advocated for fairness and social justice during his tenure in office.
